race.comment: WAGGA WAGGA (5) was plain fresh but fitter now, steps up in trip, and gets Wiggins on. Capable of sharp improvement and is a genuine threat.  KAYLEEN'S PROFIT (8) stuck on well for third at Lismore and finds another winnable race. In the mix. AU REVOIR (10) has been out of the money in recent runs including last time out when fourth over 2020m at Murwillumbah three weeks ago, beaten 2.75 lengths. Gets a great chance to atone. SOUTHOFTHEBORDER (3) grabbed a win at Toowoomba two runs back before being easily accounted for 18 days ago over 2150m at Ipswich. ENTERPRISE PRIVATE (6) returns from a lay-off and has claims on best form.
